1. "Lost in Translation" – Animated Series
Role: Sound Designer & Film Score Composer
Client: Alliance Française de Bulawayo
Description:
This animated series explores cultural identity and the beauty of diversity. Cosmos crafted an immersive score combining traditional African elements with modern beats to support the narrative. Every new episode premiers every month screening during Alliance Francaise de Bulawayo events such as World Music Day, marking a successful debut that has been praised for its powerful auditory storytelling.

2. "I Wear My Culture" – Fashion Film
Role: Film Score Composer & Sound Designer
Description:
An award-winning fashion film celebrating African heritage and personal identity, Cosmos's composition provided a rich backdrop that resonated with the visual themes. His score captured the emotional journey of the film, blending cultural pride with contemporary sounds.

3. "The Holder" – African Animated Short
Role: Sound Designer & Music Producer
Description:
"The Holder" is an Afrocentric animated short that delves into African mythology and power. Cosmos’s score combined atmospheric sounds with rhythmic African instrumentation, creating an evocative soundscape that complements the rich visuals. Currently, Cosmos and Left Hand Animation are working closely on developing this short film into a full 13-episode series.
